    "gitCommitMessage": "Crew: mobile screen + entry points (Hover wheel + Settings row)\n\nFull-screen route at /crew rendering the children + pets layer\nreturned by the backend GET /api/signals?type=crew endpoint (added\nin conductor@9e3a03b). Two entry points: a 👨‍👩‍👧 nav item in the\nHover scroll wheel after Compass, and a \"Crew\" row in the Household\nsection of Settings.\n\napp/crew.tsx (new)\n- Pull from /api/signals?type=crew on mount + pull-to-refresh.\n- Children section: per-child card with brass 1px border, faint\n  rgba(255,255,255,0.03) background, rounded 12px corners.\n    - Name (off-white 16px 600) + age (muted 12px) in header row\n    - 🏃 activities with name, schedule, location\n    - 🏫 school name + pickup time\n    - 📅 upcoming events; dates within 14 days render in brass,\n      further-out dates in muted\n- Pets section: same card style, 🐾 prefix in name, type/breed in\n  header right slot, 🩺 vet info, 📅 events same rules.\n- Empty state when no children and no pets:\n    \"Conductor hasn't found any crew members yet. They surface\n     as your history is scanned.\"\n- Loading spinner, Return link at the bottom, consistent with the\n  other full-screen routes (Vault, Horizon, Compass).\n- Type-safe child/pet shapes mirror the backend extraction schema.\n\napp/_layout.tsx\n- Registered the new \"crew\" Stack.Screen with headerShown:false,\n  matching the pattern for vault / horizon / compass.\n\napp/(tabs)/hover.tsx\n- New NAV_ITEMS entry between Compass and Settings:\n    { kind: 'nav', key: 'crew', label: 'Crew', emoji: '👨‍👩‍👧',\n      route: '/crew' }\n  Renders in the InfiniteLedger like every other nav shortcut.\n\napp/(tabs)/settings.tsx\n- Added a \"Crew\" ChevronRow in the Household section, positioned\n  after Vault. Tap pushes /crew.\n\nType-checked: zero new errors. Pre-existing tsc errors in\nmissed-cues.tsx and HealthContext.ts unchanged.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
